Sentencas: The electrochemical properties of mixed conducing ceramic-ceramic composites for proton conducting fuel cells have been investigated.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of PSFC-BCYb Composites as Cathodes for Proton Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Different ratios of Pr0.58Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3-delta-BaCe0.9Yb0.1O3-delta composites have been tested as cathodes in symmetrical cells based on BaCe0.9Y0.1O3-delta dense electrolytes.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of PSFC-BCYb Composites as Cathodes for Proton Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Impedance measurements have been carried out in the temperature range of 600-800 degrees C under wet (2.5%) air.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of PSFC-BCYb Composites as Cathodes for Proton Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Different dilutions on both oxygen partial pressure and water content have been performed as a function of the temperature in order to characterise the processes (surface reaction and charge transport) occurring at the composite electrode under oxidising conditions.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of PSFC-BCYb Composites as Cathodes for Proton Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The variation of the impedance spectra after replacing protonated water by heavy water has been studied in order to understand the role of the proton transport in the overall composite cathode operation.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of PSFC-BCYb Composites as Cathodes for Proton Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Additional four-point DC-conductivity measurements have been done under different atmospheres comprising different oxygen partial pressures and H2O/D2O saturation for composites and single materials.
Titulo: Electrochemical Properties of PSFC-BCYb Composites as Cathodes for Proton Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
